Description: Handle of Koan(?) pottery transport amphora, not specified as double-barrel by Petrie. Rectangular stamp; lyre symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.122, 34.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0104)
